          • [ - ] Nico1 - member since 22-Jun-16

            @dumpinator Wrong. A 1-0 win for Liverpool would level up the head to head record and it would then come down to GD (which would also be equal) but then come down to goals for (which would in favour of Liverpool). So if Liverpool go 1-0 up Napoli have to come out and score. Unless of course PSG fail to win. A PSG draw and a Liverpool win (by any scoreline) would see all 3 teams level on 9 points and the creation of a mini league between these 3 teams. In that scenario Liverpool would top the group as they would have 6 points in the mini league in comparison to Napoli and PSG's 5. As for 2nd place in that scenario it would be Napoli as they have the better head to head record vs PSG by virtue of away goals.
